static const char __pyx_k_GeckoModelChunk_class_for_a_chun[] = "GeckoModelChunk class for a chunk of the model.\n\n    Attributes:\n        layers (nn.ModuleList): The list of decoder layers.\n        add (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.Add): The addition function for quantization.\n        mul (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.Mul): The multiplication function for quantization.\n        tanh_mul (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.Mul): The multiplication function for tanh scaling.\n        tanh_div (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.Div): The division function for tanh scaling.\n        embed_layer_norm (LayerNorm): The layer normalization for embeddings.\n        norm (nn.Module): The normalization layer.\n        lm_head (nn.Linear): The linear layer for language modeling.\n        support_quant_stub (bool): Whether quantizer stub is supported.\n        inputs_embeds (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for input embeddings.\n        mask (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for mask.\n        pos_emb (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for position embeddings.\n        cos (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for cosine embeddings.\n        sin (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for sine embeddings.\n        past_keys (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for past keys.\n        past_values (mtk_quantization.pytorch.functional.QuantizerStub): The quantizer stub for past values.\n        cache (nn.ModuleList): The list of quantizer stubs for cache.\n        expected_num_pos_emb_inputs (int): The expected number of position embedding inputs.\n        expected_num_cache_inputs (int): The expected number of cache inputs.\n        expected_num_lora_inputs (int): The expected number of LoRA inputs.\n\n    Methods:\n        __init__(config, lora, num_layers, chunk_idx, dtype, include_tail, jit_trace, decoder_cla""ss, norm_class,\n            parallel_lora, distribute_layers): Initialize the GeckoModelChunk.\n        _add_quantizer(state_dict, temp_state_dict, state_dict_subkey, prefix, quantizer_type, quantizer):\n            Add quantizer to the state dictionary.\n        _get_single_layer_zero_lora_inputs(): Get zero LoRA inputs for a single layer.\n        scaled_tanh(hidden_states, scale): Apply scaled tanh activation.\n        forward(inputs_embeds, mask, *remainder_inputs): Forward pass for the model chunk.\n        load_weights(state_dict, state_dict_start_idx, quant_config, prefix): Load weights into the model.\n        get_jit_trace_inputs(): Get inputs for JIT tracing.\n        get_ptq_inputs(args, exp_name, lora_inputs, lora_map, file_format): Get inputs for post-training quantization.\n    ";
